			<div class="content" id="post-content-3819471">
									

<div style="text-align: center;">
<p><strong><em><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k2KrpoajFY4">I watched with glee</a><br />
<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k2KrpoajFY4">While your kings and queens</a><br />
<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k2KrpoajFY4">Fought for ten decades</a><br />
<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k2KrpoajFY4">For the gods they made</a><br />
<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k2KrpoajFY4">I shouted out</a><br />
<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k2KrpoajFY4">Who killed the Kennedys?</a><br />
<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k2KrpoajFY4">When after all</a><br />
<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k2KrpoajFY4">It was you and me</a></em></strong></p>
</div>
<hr />
<p>With thanks to the following for their critique:</p>
<p>CadaverCommander<br />
The Great Hippo<br />
EldritchCadence<br />
CaptainKirby</p>
<p>Should anyone whose articles are crosslinked here like those crosslinks/references removed, please ask and I will remove it. And if DrClef would like this whole thing taken down for screwing with his creation, I will happily do that too.</p>
<p>This 001 Proposal is part of the <a href="/doomsday-contest">Doomsday Contest</a>, representing Team &quot;End-of-the-Contest Scenario&quot; and our &quot;Tashkent-Class &quot;Cross-Pollination&quot; Scenario&quot;. The scenario is centred around two very different types of anomaly coming into contact with one another, causing things to somehow go wrong with the universe and causing an apocalypse.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">But,&nbsp;Tufto,&nbsp;isn't&nbsp;the&nbsp;Scarlet&nbsp;King&nbsp;already&nbsp;an&nbsp;SCP?</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">(WARNING:&nbsp;2317&nbsp;SPOILERS)</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>No. Or at least, only maybe. If you look into the comments of 2317, Clef makes it clear that 2317 being the SK is only an interpretation. 2317 MIGHT be the Scarlet King, or it might just be a deliberate red herring to throw people off. So I'm trying to take a similarly ambiguous position here.</p>
<p>And on that subject- this 001 is meant to be read from the perspective of an O5, as I think I imply. This is why 2317 is referred to as being the SK and not 2317-K; in the final iteration, they just straight up say that 2317 is the Devourer.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>I am sure a lot of people won't like this interpretation, or the delivery. But, hey, I figure it's worth a shot :p and as a 001 it doesn't have to be canon, so feel free to completely disregard.</p>
<p>And, as ever, you can find more of my stuff <a href="/tufto-personnel-file">here</a>.</p>

							</div>

								
