<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">...&nbsp;Okay.&nbsp;I&nbsp;think&nbsp;I&nbsp;get&nbsp;what&nbsp;the&nbsp;laws&nbsp;are.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Am&nbsp;I&nbsp;close?</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>The Law of Blood: Blood as in 'family'. Mountauk lost a brother to the Children, giving him a connection to SCP-001. Possibly why sacrifices are demanded: you must lose someone close to serve the King.<br />
The Law of Concrete: Concrete as in 'real'. The Scarlet King is not real, but everyone wants him to be, hence, the law being created from an unknown source, as you can't really give credit here. The Foundation is partly to blame, for trying to put a label on him and put him in a box.<br />
The Law of Howling: Emotion, maybe? As in despair or sorrow? 110- Mountauk was the product of spite, Robert expressed his loss (blood) into a containment procedure (concrete). And howling is an expression of grief.</p>
<p>But hey, it's just a theory. An SCP THEORY!</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>I am surprised by this approach to the Scarlet King, but it was well-written and made me think. That means you get my upvote. +1.</p>

