														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3819533">
									

<p>+1. I’m not an experienced writer, but holy hell was that a blast to read. Your proposal is a very funny yet still horrific (in a good way) depiction of the Scarlet King. The mention of other significant skips like SCP-3000, -2747 and 3125, though minor, shows clearly that no matter what horrors the Foundation faces, they WILL find a way to contain an anomaly.</p>
<p>What I found funny is how the Scarlet King, an entity far more powerful than the Apollyon 2317, is classified as safe, despite the risks the King poses.</p>

