				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tl333s" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1304786); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1304786&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610225793" alt="TL333s" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1304786)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tl333s" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1304786); return false;" >TL333s</a></span> <span class="odate time_1527860769 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">01 Jun 2018 13:46</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3820088">
									

<p>Upvoted because it's exceptionally well written, as an 001 should be, and because I upvoted kaktus's proposal.</p>
<p>Seriously.</p>
<p>You've got tremendous hooks with &quot;<span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Keter</span> Safe&quot;, Montauk's name, and the burgeoning mystery of &quot;why the fuck don't we need to contain <em>the Scarlet goddamn King</em>?&quot; But the whole time, I couldn't not be bothered by first, we've already got 2317, and second, your &quot;oh, well that's not <em>really</em> the Scarlet King&quot;. I mean, Clef's comment above justifies it, so it's fine, but it still bothered me.</p>
<p>But I can't let it bother me because There Is a Canon Now. This is worthy of upvotes, so it gets upvotes! Or, well, one, because that's all I got. :B</p>
<p>That said, the whirling cacophony of anti-modernism, struggling with 231, and opposition to imperialism and/or cultural appropriation (which is not bad in and of itself) is the weirdest soup. I cannot grasp what you were trying to say with this, if, indeed, you were trying to say anything at all.</p>

							</div>

								
					
